1
00:00:15,071 --> 00:00:17,881
[This show contains AI-generated footage]

2
00:00:17,881 --> 00:00:21,291
The first short drama competition show in Korea,

3
00:00:21,291 --> 00:00:24,291
Director's Arena welcomes you!

4
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:27,911
The 33 directors decided to challenge themselves.

5
00:00:27,911 --> 00:00:31,071
Complete a 90-second teaser.

6
00:00:31,071 --> 00:00:33,331
[The mission is difficult from Round 1]

7
00:00:33,331 --> 00:00:36,541
I've directed and produced
over 20 short-form dramas.

8
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:40,321
[Everyone is a strong contender]

9
00:00:40,321 --> 00:00:43,311
[The eye-popping high-quality teasers]

10
00:00:43,821 --> 00:00:46,621
[Many people were given a chance to survive]

11
00:00:47,121 --> 00:00:49,691
[And then, this one teaser appeared]

12
00:00:49,691 --> 00:00:51,641
What's this?

13
00:00:51,641 --> 00:00:54,741
[Totally absorbed]

14
00:00:54,741 --> 00:00:57,771
[Everyone cheered when she appeared]

15
00:00:57,771 --> 00:01:00,101
[The first survivor, Director Han Soo Ji]

16
00:01:00,101 --> 00:01:02,361
Finally, Cha Tae Hyun's favorite.

17
00:01:02,361 --> 00:01:04,421
[And another person who got everyone's attention]

18
00:01:05,131 --> 00:01:07,121
It was very disappointing.

19
00:01:07,121 --> 00:01:09,841
[Since he didn't meet the expectations]

20
00:01:10,551 --> 00:01:13,111
[He became the first one to be eliminated]

21
00:01:13,111 --> 00:01:14,721
What was that?

22
00:01:14,721 --> 00:01:18,351
It is a shame, but please return to
your seat and continue voting.

23
00:01:19,401 --> 00:01:20,931
[And]

24
00:01:20,931 --> 00:01:23,691
- Huh? He looks familiar.
- Very familiar.

25
00:01:23,691 --> 00:01:25,401
Director Lee Yoo Jin.

26
00:01:25,401 --> 00:01:27,621
I want to win first place.

27
00:01:27,621 --> 00:01:30,761
Let's start now. Play the video.

28
00:01:30,761 --> 00:01:32,451
[Everyone was absorbed]

29
00:01:32,451 --> 00:01:34,941
[Special cameo appearances]

30
00:01:35,421 --> 00:01:36,681
[Laughing out loud]

31
00:01:36,681 --> 00:01:38,271
[Whoa]

32
00:01:38,271 --> 00:01:40,291
[The stop count never went up]

33
00:01:40,291 --> 00:01:43,431
[Explosive reaction]

34
00:01:43,431 --> 00:01:45,921
For the first time, we have zero stops.

35
00:01:45,921 --> 00:01:49,671
You survived cleanly, Director Lee Yoo Jin.

36
00:01:49,671 --> 00:01:52,291
[Which director will surpass his record?]

37
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:55,381
Let's meet the next director.

38
00:01:55,381 --> 00:01:59,521
The director of "Is This Marriage Valid?"
Please come forward.

39
00:01:59,521 --> 00:02:02,001
Her eyes are red.

40
00:02:02,001 --> 00:02:03,901
She kept them open for too long.

41
00:02:03,901 --> 00:02:06,751
[What do I do?]

42
00:02:07,701 --> 00:02:10,161
[Everyone is supportive on this show]

43
00:02:10,161 --> 00:02:12,991
Thank you. Gosh!

44
00:02:12,991 --> 00:02:14,991
It's finally time. It's time.

45
00:02:14,991 --> 00:02:17,351
Win first place. First place.

46
00:02:17,351 --> 00:02:20,341
- She's the No. 1 director.
- No. 1 in short dramas.

47
00:02:20,341 --> 00:02:22,641
Gosh, I'm dying.

48
00:02:22,641 --> 00:02:23,781
[Exhaling]

49
00:02:23,781 --> 00:02:25,901
[Exhaling]

50
00:02:25,901 --> 00:02:29,491
Director Park So Rang, welcome.

51
00:02:29,491 --> 00:02:30,911
Hello.

52
00:02:30,911 --> 00:02:34,931
I know you're nervous,
but please introduce yourself.

53
00:02:34,931 --> 00:02:38,901
I can do it. I can do it. I can do it.

54
00:02:38,901 --> 00:02:40,951
You can do it!

55
00:02:41,751 --> 00:02:43,341
That was like "Miss Trot."

56
00:02:43,341 --> 00:02:45,011
[LOL]

57
00:02:45,011 --> 00:02:48,691
Hello, I climbed up to No. 1
as soon as I debuted.

58
00:02:48,691 --> 00:02:52,441
The No. 1 short drama director, Park So Rang.

59
00:02:53,671 --> 00:02:56,981
- She's nervous for no reason.
- Why are you nervous?

60
00:02:56,981 --> 00:02:58,891
- I know.
- I was curious.

61
00:02:58,891 --> 00:03:02,851
"Eldest Daughter's Marriage Life"
streamed on Vigloo last year.

62
00:03:02,851 --> 00:03:05,351
That was my debut work.

63
00:03:05,351 --> 00:03:10,001
And a week ago, a Vigloo short called,
"I Can Touch You"

64
00:03:10,001 --> 00:03:12,311
finished filming last week.

65
00:03:13,321 --> 00:03:18,241
I watched a lot of romance
dramas and studied directing.

66
00:03:18,241 --> 00:03:21,181
[Detailed acting directions]

67
00:03:21,181 --> 00:03:24,271
- How dare you touch my woman?
- Okay.

68
00:03:24,271 --> 00:03:26,201
Let's get more emotional.

69
00:03:26,201 --> 00:03:28,931
[A rising star, a new director's
exciting rebellion]

70
00:03:28,931 --> 00:03:32,361
There are countless short dramas,

71
00:03:32,361 --> 00:03:35,471
but yours ranked No. 1. What's the secret?

72
00:03:35,471 --> 00:03:37,931
There are three, in my opinion.

73
00:03:37,931 --> 00:03:42,691
First is an attitude that leads people to pay.

74
00:03:42,691 --> 00:03:46,371
Since I'm focused on romance, the second is

75
00:03:46,371 --> 00:03:50,281
a handsome male lead who can
flutter women's hearts.

76
00:03:50,281 --> 00:03:56,341
And third is a directing skill
that draws people in.

77
00:03:56,341 --> 00:03:57,811
[True, true]

78
00:03:57,811 --> 00:03:59,981
She's eloquent.

79
00:03:59,981 --> 00:04:01,931
I want to ask you something.

80
00:04:01,931 --> 00:04:04,921
What do you think your rank in Round 1 will be?

81
00:04:04,921 --> 00:04:07,111
- My rank?
- Yes.

82
00:04:07,111 --> 00:04:08,751
First place?

83
00:04:08,751 --> 00:04:11,021
[She's No. 1 in confidence, too]

84
00:04:11,021 --> 00:04:15,491
But the best you can do
is to be in joint first place.

85
00:04:15,491 --> 00:04:18,451
- One person got zero stops already.
- That's true.

86
00:04:18,451 --> 00:04:21,001
Director Lee Yoo Jin got zero stops.

87
00:04:21,001 --> 00:04:23,671
For the first time, we have zero stops.

88
00:04:23,671 --> 00:04:27,981
You survived cleanly, Director Lee Yoo Jin.

89
00:04:27,981 --> 00:04:29,971
[First to get zero stops]

90
00:04:29,971 --> 00:04:34,181
Would you be able to get zero stops, too?

91
00:04:34,181 --> 00:04:36,581
I think I'll win first place.

92
00:04:36,581 --> 00:04:38,411
[Totally confident]

93
00:04:38,411 --> 00:04:42,391
This short drama is about a runaway bride

94
00:04:42,391 --> 00:04:46,021
encountering her first love.

95
00:04:46,021 --> 00:04:50,241
- The genre is passionate romance.
- Passionate romance.

96
00:04:50,241 --> 00:04:51,891
She knows exactly.

97
00:04:51,891 --> 00:04:53,811
She knows what people like.

98
00:04:53,811 --> 00:04:55,821
Her focus is clear.

99
00:04:55,821 --> 00:04:57,491
She said "passionate romance" already.

100
00:04:57,491 --> 00:04:59,491
She's already using a cheat key.

101
00:04:59,491 --> 00:05:00,881
I'm curious.

102
00:05:01,821 --> 00:05:04,041
[70 people with different tastes]

103
00:05:04,041 --> 00:05:08,421
[Will passionate romance work?]

104
00:05:09,301 --> 00:05:12,151
I was... I was so nervous.

105
00:05:12,151 --> 00:05:14,231
[Is This Marriage Valid?]

106
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,591
I can't control myself. How can I with you?

107
00:05:16,591 --> 00:05:18,161
Forget about everything tonight.

108
00:05:18,161 --> 00:05:20,211
I can't control myself. How can I with you?

109
00:05:20,211 --> 00:05:21,871
[This is it!]

110
00:05:21,871 --> 00:05:23,301
I can't control myself.

111
00:05:23,301 --> 00:05:26,111
[A powerful start!]

112
00:05:28,281 --> 00:05:31,461
- From the beginning?
- So, this is it.

113
00:05:31,461 --> 00:05:34,191
Come on. How can you not watch this?

114
00:05:34,191 --> 00:05:36,531
[Park So Rang's "Is this Marriage Valid?"]

115
00:05:36,531 --> 00:05:38,681
- Forget about everything tonight.
- Game over.

116
00:05:38,681 --> 00:05:39,861
[Beginning of tragedy]

117
00:05:39,861 --> 00:05:43,121
This is the only way to repay my parents.

118
00:05:43,121 --> 00:05:45,221
[The adultery video went viral
on her wedding day]

119
00:05:45,221 --> 00:05:47,501
I can't control myself. How can I with you?

120
00:05:47,501 --> 00:05:50,841
- But this is...
- You're different. You turn me on.

121
00:05:50,841 --> 00:05:53,261
Marriage is a formality.
I'll reserve my love for you.

122
00:05:53,261 --> 00:05:55,921
I was able to endure your abuse.

123
00:05:55,921 --> 00:05:58,131
- But this is...
- I told you not to cry.

124
00:05:58,131 --> 00:06:00,351
This marriage is annulled.

125
00:06:01,461 --> 00:06:03,721
What are you doing? Stop her!

126
00:06:05,171 --> 00:06:08,071
[Voting starts]

127
00:06:08,071 --> 00:06:10,941
This is fun. This is fun.

128
00:06:10,941 --> 00:06:12,601
Game over.

129
00:06:14,281 --> 00:06:16,241
[Voting starts]

130
00:06:16,241 --> 00:06:17,651
Game over.

131
00:06:20,991 --> 00:06:22,841
Ji Han?

132
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:25,411
I reunited with my first love
as my wedding was called off.

133
00:06:25,411 --> 00:06:27,601
This is totally a short drama.

134
00:06:27,601 --> 00:06:29,841
[The stop count won't go up]

135
00:06:29,841 --> 00:06:31,581
Ji Han?

136
00:06:31,581 --> 00:06:33,961
[Will the miracle of zero stops happen again?]

137
00:06:33,961 --> 00:06:36,321
Why would you run away from your wedding?

138
00:06:36,321 --> 00:06:38,121
Do you have a secret lover or something?

139
00:06:38,121 --> 00:06:41,861
What? Forget it. Thank you for your help.

140
00:06:41,861 --> 00:06:43,621
[Stop count: 1]

141
00:06:43,621 --> 00:06:46,721
[Her dream to win first place ends]

142
00:06:46,721 --> 00:06:49,041
[Solid first place]

143
00:06:50,321 --> 00:06:53,391
Do you have a place to go?
Do you want my help or not?

144
00:06:53,391 --> 00:06:55,071
[The heartbroken bride starts living with him]

145
00:06:55,071 --> 00:06:57,411
Under one condition. You have to become my wife.

146
00:06:57,411 --> 00:06:59,221
- Wife?
- Shouldn't you pay the price?

147
00:06:59,221 --> 00:07:02,721
This is how I can protect you.
I won't let you go, Lee Ye Na.

148
00:07:02,721 --> 00:07:06,541
How dare you screw me over?
Did you forget who I am?

149
00:07:06,541 --> 00:07:08,121
I'm sorry. Forgive me.

150
00:07:08,121 --> 00:07:10,921
You humiliated me. You need to be punished.

151
00:07:10,921 --> 00:07:12,521
Ye Na!

152
00:07:12,521 --> 00:07:15,101
- I can see people paying for this.
- Ye Na!

153
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:17,741
[Unlike her expectation, the stop count goes up]

154
00:07:17,741 --> 00:07:20,491
[Stop count: 11]

155
00:07:20,491 --> 00:07:22,031
How dare you hurt my woman?

156
00:07:22,031 --> 00:07:23,961
I have a woman I need to protect with my life.

157
00:07:23,961 --> 00:07:25,051
- Let's get married.
- Sunbae.

158
00:07:25,051 --> 00:07:26,001
No going back.

159
00:07:26,001 --> 00:07:30,191
You'd better not leave me at the altar, either.

160
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:33,891
Hold on. I need to check something first.

161
00:07:33,891 --> 00:07:36,451
Is This Marriage Valid?

162
00:07:39,931 --> 00:07:41,091
[So fun!]

163
00:07:41,091 --> 00:07:47,221
Director Park So Rang gets a chance
to survive with 15 stops.

164
00:07:47,221 --> 00:07:51,531
First of all, it didn't go the way you wanted.

165
00:07:51,531 --> 00:07:53,091
[Disappointed]

166
00:07:53,091 --> 00:07:56,671
If I were watching this on my phone,

167
00:07:56,671 --> 00:07:58,921
I wouldn't know where to skip.

168
00:07:58,921 --> 00:08:01,151
Whenever I tried, the next scene already started.

169
00:08:01,151 --> 00:08:03,641
It was intense from the start.

170
00:08:03,641 --> 00:08:06,491
I wonder how you'll reach the peak at the end.

171
00:08:06,491 --> 00:08:09,011
Will the excitement reach its peak

172
00:08:09,011 --> 00:08:12,051
or will there be a twist in the plot?

173
00:08:12,051 --> 00:08:16,131
I think that's the challenge you'll face.

174
00:08:16,131 --> 00:08:19,441
But the teaser was very provocative.

175
00:08:19,441 --> 00:08:23,361
The moment I thought my dopamine peaked,

176
00:08:23,361 --> 00:08:27,641
I realized I definitely am Korean.

177
00:08:27,641 --> 00:08:30,001
That was dopamine itself.

178
00:08:30,001 --> 00:08:32,421
The first scene was too powerful.

179
00:08:32,421 --> 00:08:33,411
What did you think, Director Lee?

180
00:08:33,411 --> 00:08:37,761
I think the 15 votes were...

181
00:08:37,761 --> 00:08:39,971
based on personal taste.

182
00:08:39,971 --> 00:08:42,861
I think production companies would love you.

183
00:08:42,861 --> 00:08:46,421
- Thank you.
- She'll win first place at this rate.

184
00:08:46,421 --> 00:08:50,981
It shows how a short drama should be.

185
00:08:50,981 --> 00:08:52,731
- A model short.
- It was fun.

186
00:08:52,731 --> 00:08:55,221
- Yes.
- You were aiming for first place.

187
00:08:55,221 --> 00:08:58,621
And you ranked No. 1 as you debuted.

188
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:00,561
You must be disappointed right now.

189
00:09:00,561 --> 00:09:02,681
Yes, I'm disappointed.

190
00:09:03,531 --> 00:09:05,211
Why did you press the stop?

191
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,981
Why is that?

192
00:09:08,911 --> 00:09:11,071
I was a bit disappointed.

193
00:09:11,071 --> 00:09:14,581
I think they don't understand short dramas.

194
00:09:15,411 --> 00:09:19,221
Let's welcome the next director, then.

195
00:09:19,221 --> 00:09:23,101
"I Decided Not to be Born to Save Mom."

196
00:09:23,101 --> 00:09:25,831
- Come forward.
- Fighting!

197
00:09:25,831 --> 00:09:28,311
The title is so sad already.

198
00:09:28,311 --> 00:09:30,831
It sounds... It sounds sad.

199
00:09:30,831 --> 00:09:33,741
That looks good. I can tell from the poster.

200
00:09:33,741 --> 00:09:37,751
- It feels like Netflix content.
- I know.

201
00:09:37,751 --> 00:09:43,471
Hello, I act, direct, produce, write,
and all sorts of things.

202
00:09:43,471 --> 00:09:46,251
I'm Lee Beom Gyu.

203
00:09:46,251 --> 00:09:48,201
You have a stronger presence in person.

204
00:09:48,201 --> 00:09:50,231
Really? I don't look good on camera?

205
00:09:50,231 --> 00:09:53,041
- No, that's not what I mean.
- I was kidding.

206
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:55,731
I'm trying to break the ice. I'm nervous. Hello.

207
00:09:55,731 --> 00:09:58,421
What made you apply to the show?

208
00:09:58,421 --> 00:10:02,031
I've been receiving a lot of support
for my work, thankfully.

209
00:10:02,031 --> 00:10:03,701
Thank you. But...

210
00:10:03,701 --> 00:10:06,601
[A very talkative man]

211
00:10:06,601 --> 00:10:09,421
But... But hear me out, everyone.

212
00:10:09,421 --> 00:10:11,291
Focus. But...

213
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:17,431
[One-man talk show went on for a long time]

214
00:10:17,921 --> 00:10:20,541
- I feel drained. Please leave.
- I feel drained, too.

215
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:22,371
Are you drained?

216
00:10:22,371 --> 00:10:25,401
I can stay longer because
I have two hours of parking.

217
00:10:26,221 --> 00:10:29,811
I'm not sure how to feel about this.

218
00:10:29,811 --> 00:10:31,681
What's with your nickname?

219
00:10:31,681 --> 00:10:33,701
"My Target is Cha Tae Hyun"?

220
00:10:33,701 --> 00:10:35,621
Why? Why?

221
00:10:35,621 --> 00:10:39,521
I chose him as my target audience

222
00:10:39,521 --> 00:10:45,041
because I decided to go into acting
after I first saw "My Sassy Girl."

223
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:49,091
And I recently had a daughter in January.

224
00:10:49,091 --> 00:10:50,931
I didn't give birth, but my wife did.

225
00:10:50,931 --> 00:10:52,841
You had her together.

226
00:10:52,841 --> 00:10:54,171
Together?

227
00:10:54,171 --> 00:10:59,751
You're my role model for succeeding
in both life and work.

228
00:10:59,751 --> 00:11:01,421
- Your role model in life.
- Yes.

229
00:11:01,421 --> 00:11:03,811
I love you. I jongyeong* you. I respect you.
(Means "respect")

230
00:11:03,811 --> 00:11:05,321
Thank you.

231
00:11:05,321 --> 00:11:07,381
"Jongyeong" and "respect" mean the same thing.

232
00:11:07,381 --> 00:11:10,031
- Please edit it out.
- You wanted to emphasize that.

233
00:11:10,031 --> 00:11:15,141
- Yes, I did.
- I heard you exchange texts with Tae Hyun.

234
00:11:15,141 --> 00:11:17,641
Yes. Was it 13 years ago?

235
00:11:17,641 --> 00:11:19,831
- You were in the Georgia Coffee commercial.
- I know.

236
00:11:19,831 --> 00:11:23,451
I told him the same thing then.
That I started acting because of him.

237
00:11:23,451 --> 00:11:26,321
I jumped into it because he made it look so easy.

238
00:11:26,321 --> 00:11:30,471
- And he was stunned...
- That could mean many things.

239
00:11:30,471 --> 00:11:32,401
[I'll just laugh]

240
00:11:32,401 --> 00:11:34,021
He made it look easy.

241
00:11:34,021 --> 00:11:35,631
[Talking a lot and messing up a lot]

242
00:11:35,631 --> 00:11:40,441
And I should mention that I've met
each of you before.

243
00:11:40,441 --> 00:11:43,021
Mr. Jang Keun Suk, about 10 years ago,

244
00:11:43,021 --> 00:11:45,831
I met you on the set of the
Galaxy Player commercial.

245
00:11:45,831 --> 00:11:47,341
I worked on that set, too.

246
00:11:47,341 --> 00:11:49,431
I met you in the elevator.

247
00:11:49,431 --> 00:11:53,781
And I met Ms. Jang Do Yeon
when I went to see "Comedy Big League."

248
00:11:53,781 --> 00:11:56,801
- We met in Sangam-dong.
- Yes, 10 years ago.

249
00:11:56,801 --> 00:12:01,331
I met Director Lee Byeong Heon
at Yang Hyun Min's wedding.

250
00:12:01,331 --> 00:12:02,971
You stood next to me during a photo shoot.

251
00:12:02,971 --> 00:12:05,231
[Unbelievable]

252
00:12:05,231 --> 00:12:07,031
[Laughing]

253
00:12:07,031 --> 00:12:08,131
[Laughing again]

254
00:12:08,131 --> 00:12:09,811
During the group photo shoot,

255
00:12:09,811 --> 00:12:12,181
- I was next to Shin Ha Kyun.
- I'll look it up.

256
00:12:12,181 --> 00:12:16,021
[Lee Byeong Heon / Shin Ha Kyun / Lee Beom Gyu]

257
00:12:16,021 --> 00:12:18,421
We crossed paths in one way or another.

258
00:12:18,421 --> 00:12:22,761
I took a closer look at this, Beom Gyu.

259
00:12:22,761 --> 00:12:25,601
I see the actors' names at the top.

260
00:12:25,601 --> 00:12:29,701
You made it look like a movie poster.

261
00:12:29,701 --> 00:12:33,561
The tagline is, "There's never been
a short-form like this before."

262
00:12:33,561 --> 00:12:39,841
I thought a short drama
could be more like a film.

263
00:12:39,841 --> 00:12:41,221
In my opinion,

264
00:12:41,221 --> 00:12:44,401
short dramas are often about
dopamine, passionate romance,

265
00:12:44,401 --> 00:12:46,111
kissing, and stuff like that.

266
00:12:46,111 --> 00:12:48,871
I wanted to do less of that.

267
00:12:48,871 --> 00:12:51,671
It's for people who are tired
of provocative content.

268
00:12:51,671 --> 00:12:57,221
I think it's more heartwarming,
and it lets you think.

269
00:12:57,221 --> 00:12:59,221
I think that's what its strength is.

270
00:12:59,221 --> 00:13:01,571
Please introduce your work.

271
00:13:01,571 --> 00:13:03,671
Yes. I really am nervous.

272
00:13:03,671 --> 00:13:06,131
You talk too much for someone who's nervous.

273
00:13:06,131 --> 00:13:08,121
What are you talking about?

274
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:11,591
A man's mother died from domestic violence.

275
00:13:11,591 --> 00:13:17,171
He tries to end his life because
he's fed up with living with the trauma.

276
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:21,261
But he travels back in time before
his mother was married.

277
00:13:21,261 --> 00:13:24,671
He finds out this woman is his mother and

278
00:13:24,671 --> 00:13:26,711
in order to stop her from marrying his father,

279
00:13:26,711 --> 00:13:29,651
he pretends to be in love with her.

280
00:13:29,651 --> 00:13:32,561
Ah! With his mom?

281
00:13:32,561 --> 00:13:34,821
And I decided to write this story because...

282
00:13:34,821 --> 00:13:38,791
- A friend of mine is in Jung Sik's Band.
- Yes, Jung Sik.

283
00:13:38,791 --> 00:13:44,021
About three years ago,
we were chugging alcohol-

284
00:13:44,021 --> 00:13:45,891
While we were drinking...

285
00:13:45,891 --> 00:13:49,171
<i>♫ After living inside my mom ♫</i>

286
00:13:49,171 --> 00:13:52,161
<i>♫ I came out to heaven ♫</i>

287
00:13:52,161 --> 00:13:58,191
<i>♫ And I saw the world ♫</i>

288
00:13:58,191 --> 00:14:01,301
<i>♫ My first love ♫</i>

289
00:14:01,301 --> 00:14:03,611
<i>♫ My everything ♫</i>

290
00:14:03,611 --> 00:14:07,751
<i>♫ Mom, Mom ♫</i>

291
00:14:07,751 --> 00:14:09,821
I can see the whole movie.

292
00:14:09,821 --> 00:14:12,321
I'll try coming up with something.

293
00:14:13,071 --> 00:14:16,271
- He did the OST?
- He did.

294
00:14:16,271 --> 00:14:19,521
The story isn't complete without his song.

295
00:14:19,521 --> 00:14:22,281
Wow. He seems to know everyone.

296
00:14:22,281 --> 00:14:25,371
I see actor Cha Sun Woo.

297
00:14:25,371 --> 00:14:27,851
- Na Hae Ryung.
- Dong Hyun Bae, too.

298
00:14:27,851 --> 00:14:31,741
- Right?
- So many people helped me.

299
00:14:31,741 --> 00:14:33,621
[Director Lee Beom Gyu's teaser set]

300
00:14:33,621 --> 00:14:37,831
Shoot here and here. Insert this part right here.

301
00:14:37,831 --> 00:14:38,891
[Too much passion]

302
00:14:38,891 --> 00:14:41,361
Everyone will gather here.

303
00:14:41,361 --> 00:14:43,331
Too fast! Too fast!

304
00:14:43,331 --> 00:14:45,031
Action.

305
00:14:45,031 --> 00:14:47,501
[Cha Sun Woo, getting in the zone right away]

306
00:14:47,501 --> 00:14:49,011
Cut, okay.

307
00:14:49,011 --> 00:14:50,801
- Cut.
- Let's try this.

308
00:14:50,801 --> 00:14:52,191
[Hyper]

309
00:14:52,191 --> 00:14:54,051
- You can talk to me from there.
- No, no.

310
00:14:54,051 --> 00:14:56,441
[A beach scene]

311
00:14:57,341 --> 00:14:59,591
Oppa, I'm really not cold.

312
00:14:59,591 --> 00:15:02,671
Gosh, did you hear me?

313
00:15:02,671 --> 00:15:05,181
[Freaking out again]

314
00:15:05,181 --> 00:15:08,151
[He appears as an actor, too]

315
00:15:08,151 --> 00:15:10,201
It's a two-person shot. Get ready and go.

316
00:15:10,201 --> 00:15:13,041
Don't die. It's wrong to die.

317
00:15:13,841 --> 00:15:16,301
Jung Sik! Jung Sik!

318
00:15:17,091 --> 00:15:18,381
Jung Sik.

319
00:15:18,381 --> 00:15:20,421
[It hurts...]

320
00:15:20,421 --> 00:15:22,621
Cut. Was that okay?

321
00:15:23,371 --> 00:15:24,881
Did it turn out well?

322
00:15:24,881 --> 00:15:27,041
I think this is a concrete floor.

323
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:29,351
- It turned out well. It's great.
- Okay.

324
00:15:29,351 --> 00:15:33,331
You're watching the Lee Beom Gyu Show.

325
00:15:33,331 --> 00:15:37,951
Beom Gyu, I really hope you pass.

326
00:15:37,951 --> 00:15:40,331
- Shall we go?
- Fighting.

327
00:15:40,331 --> 00:15:44,181
[What kind of short drama did he create?]

328
00:15:44,181 --> 00:15:46,891
Let's be objective here.

329
00:15:46,891 --> 00:15:49,281
Gosh, I hope it's good.

330
00:15:50,621 --> 00:15:53,721
I'm curious. Please be good.

331
00:15:53,721 --> 00:15:55,771
[I Decided Not to be Born to Save Mom]

332
00:15:55,771 --> 00:15:57,051
[Lee Beom Gyu's "I Decided Not to
be Born to Save Mom"]

333
00:15:57,051 --> 00:15:59,621
If I weren't born...

334
00:15:59,621 --> 00:16:01,831
[Lee Beom Gyu's "I Decided Not to
be Born to Save Mom"]

335
00:16:01,831 --> 00:16:04,161
would my mom still be alive?

336
00:16:04,161 --> 00:16:05,601
[1989]

337
00:16:05,601 --> 00:16:07,011
It's wrong to die.

338
00:16:07,011 --> 00:16:08,561
Jung Sik.

339
00:16:08,561 --> 00:16:10,821
<i>♫ I try to go back in time ♫</i>

340
00:16:10,821 --> 00:16:15,301
I've never met her before,
but I somehow missed her.

341
00:16:15,301 --> 00:16:17,251
You got something here.

342
00:16:18,231 --> 00:16:20,151
Let's set our wedding date.

343
00:16:22,001 --> 00:16:24,161
Forget about that man.

344
00:16:27,171 --> 00:16:29,651
[Voting starts]

345
00:16:30,601 --> 00:16:32,231
Bastard.

346
00:16:36,811 --> 00:16:38,431
Hey!

347
00:16:38,431 --> 00:16:40,321
[As soon as the voting starts]

348
00:16:40,321 --> 00:16:42,721
[the stop count spikes]

349
00:16:42,721 --> 00:16:45,601
[Watching without caring]

350
00:16:46,901 --> 00:16:49,911
<i>♫ After living inside my mom ♫</i>

351
00:16:49,911 --> 00:16:53,521
If I'm born, Mom will die.

352
00:16:55,071 --> 00:16:58,821
Prove whether you can prevail with love.

353
00:16:58,821 --> 00:17:00,731
I love you.

354
00:17:02,081 --> 00:17:05,091
[It's more provocative than expected...]

355
00:17:05,091 --> 00:17:07,931
- Who are you?
- People always label things.

356
00:17:07,931 --> 00:17:12,341
I have to pretend to be in love
with someone I want to call Mom.

357
00:17:12,341 --> 00:17:15,621
Because I was born to make you happy.

358
00:17:15,621 --> 00:17:18,121
[What?]

359
00:17:18,121 --> 00:17:20,221
[Can't hear the lines because of the music]

360
00:17:20,221 --> 00:17:23,421
- You'll die if you choose the child.
- I know it's my son.

361
00:17:23,421 --> 00:17:25,201
Let's pray.

362
00:17:30,021 --> 00:17:32,411
Don't cry.

363
00:17:32,411 --> 00:17:34,651
I love you.

364
00:17:35,961 --> 00:17:39,011
[Stop count: 22]

365
00:17:39,811 --> 00:17:42,021
[I Decided Not to be Born to Save Mom]

366
00:17:42,021 --> 00:17:43,771
That was good.

367
00:17:44,601 --> 00:17:47,001
[The studio went quiet]

368
00:17:47,001 --> 00:17:50,211
- If I got eliminated...
- Why am I sad?

369
00:17:50,211 --> 00:17:52,421
I like the song.

370
00:17:52,421 --> 00:17:55,021
You get a chance to survive.

371
00:17:55,021 --> 00:17:57,131
It's not easy to be eliminated.

372
00:17:57,131 --> 00:17:59,051
[What does he mean?]

373
00:17:59,051 --> 00:18:01,611
- What are you saying?
- What do you mean?

374
00:18:03,161 --> 00:18:05,381
Are you eliminating two already?

375
00:18:05,381 --> 00:18:06,951
[What did I do? / Eliminated]

376
00:18:06,951 --> 00:18:08,271
How about Director Seo?

377
00:18:08,271 --> 00:18:10,281
I'm saying he managed to pull it off.

378
00:18:10,281 --> 00:18:12,141
[Leave me alone]

379
00:18:12,141 --> 00:18:15,441
[His stop count went up the fastest]

380
00:18:15,441 --> 00:18:17,891
[and his teaser stopped playing]

381
00:18:17,891 --> 00:18:20,861
[The first person to be eliminated]

382
00:18:20,861 --> 00:18:23,251
[He shocked everyone in the studio]

383
00:18:23,251 --> 00:18:25,281
Getting people to talk is most crucial.

384
00:18:25,281 --> 00:18:28,231
Right. He's No. 1 in that regard.

385
00:18:28,231 --> 00:18:31,221
Please return to your seat and continue voting.

386
00:18:31,221 --> 00:18:33,601
[Still voting as a viewer]

387
00:18:33,601 --> 00:18:37,701
You expressed your worldview more than anyone.

388
00:18:37,701 --> 00:18:39,501
That's the impression I got.

389
00:18:39,501 --> 00:18:44,361
But if I didn't hear your explanation

390
00:18:44,361 --> 00:18:46,271
before watching this,

391
00:18:46,271 --> 00:18:49,421
would I have understood the plot?

392
00:18:49,421 --> 00:18:52,461
I'm not so sure.

393
00:18:52,461 --> 00:18:56,251
I liked the fast pace, but it wasn't very clear

394
00:18:56,251 --> 00:18:58,631
what you were trying to say.

395
00:18:58,631 --> 00:19:00,811
I thought that was a shame.

396
00:19:00,811 --> 00:19:03,011
I didn't push the button, but...

397
00:19:03,011 --> 00:19:04,741
[Thank you]

398
00:19:04,741 --> 00:19:07,461
one thing bothered me.

399
00:19:07,461 --> 00:19:11,101
Jung Sik's song stood out too much.

400
00:19:12,421 --> 00:19:14,041
It could've been a mixing issue,

401
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:16,201
but you should've added captions.

402
00:19:16,201 --> 00:19:19,621
I couldn't hear the lines well from here.

403
00:19:19,621 --> 00:19:22,931
I made a version with captions, too.

404
00:19:22,931 --> 00:19:24,471
I thought about this a lot.

405
00:19:24,471 --> 00:19:26,261
Since I've made two short dramas,

406
00:19:26,261 --> 00:19:29,161
I know that you need captions.

407
00:19:29,161 --> 00:19:31,001
I know this is a competition,

408
00:19:31,001 --> 00:19:33,671
but my actors and crew were behind this.

409
00:19:33,671 --> 00:19:36,421
I didn't want the captions to steal the show.

410
00:19:36,421 --> 00:19:40,401
Since it's only 90 seconds long,
I decided to remove them.

411
00:19:40,401 --> 00:19:43,011
I can't ask Beom Gyu any questions.

412
00:19:43,011 --> 00:19:44,881
[LOL]

413
00:19:44,881 --> 00:19:48,841
[Let's give our ears a break...]

414
00:19:50,371 --> 00:19:52,861
[Suddenly, the studio turned red]

415
00:19:52,861 --> 00:19:56,071
It's like a cover of a novel.

416
00:19:56,071 --> 00:20:00,391
That one reminded me of a piece of literature.

417
00:20:00,391 --> 00:20:03,241
- Finally.
- I was curious about this one.

418
00:20:03,241 --> 00:20:05,141
[Coming up]

419
00:20:05,141 --> 00:20:07,661
Reminds me of Park Chan Wook.

420
00:20:07,661 --> 00:20:09,251
Like "Old Boy."

421
00:20:09,251 --> 00:20:11,721
How will she make 50 episodes of that?

422
00:20:11,721 --> 00:20:15,031
There's no story. There isn't one.

423
00:20:15,031 --> 00:20:19,211
[Who's this director?]

424
00:20:19,931 --> 00:20:24,951
I'm Yeo Ha Ni. I'll die if I can't debut.

425
00:20:24,951 --> 00:20:26,931
Have you considered the budget?

426
00:20:26,931 --> 00:20:28,991
No, I'll spend whatever is given.

427
00:20:28,991 --> 00:20:31,211
I'll spend a million won if that's what I get.

428
00:20:31,211 --> 00:20:34,291
I'm not in a position to choose right now.

429
00:20:34,291 --> 00:20:36,531
I really want to debut this time.

430
00:20:37,371 --> 00:20:39,721
I studied film for a long time.

431
00:20:39,721 --> 00:20:42,721
I worked an office job after returning to Korea.

432
00:20:42,721 --> 00:20:47,201
I worked hard on directing a film,
but I haven't been able to debut yet.

433
00:20:47,201 --> 00:20:50,031
I could tell she lived abroad. You know?

434
00:20:50,031 --> 00:20:52,361
I went to an international
elementary school in India.

435
00:20:52,361 --> 00:20:53,761
I went to middle and high school in Australia.

436
00:20:53,761 --> 00:20:56,951
And I went to college in the UK.

437
00:20:56,951 --> 00:20:59,411
She's an elite. She is.

438
00:20:59,411 --> 00:21:02,141
The story is quite sexy, you know?

439
00:21:02,141 --> 00:21:05,391
Like sexy time. Sexy scenes.

440
00:21:05,391 --> 00:21:08,891
I don't think my mom knows
what the script is about.

441
00:21:08,891 --> 00:21:12,981
I browsed Lehzin Snack, and not many are R-rated.

442
00:21:12,981 --> 00:21:15,601
Can it be R-rated?

443
00:21:15,601 --> 00:21:17,841
I want to... I want to shoot now.

444
00:21:17,841 --> 00:21:19,561
I can't wait to write it.

445
00:21:19,561 --> 00:21:23,031
Please move around like this. Up and down.

446
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:27,311
[Director Yeo Ha Ni has
a strong voice as an artist]

447
00:21:27,311 --> 00:21:29,641
[What's "Don't Let the Night Know
About Your Forbidden Love" about?]

448
00:21:29,641 --> 00:21:34,711
I wondered about an insomniac's pain and love.

449
00:21:34,711 --> 00:21:36,091
That's how it was created.

450
00:21:36,091 --> 00:21:40,221
The woman who suffers from insomnia
due to her husband's abuse

451
00:21:40,221 --> 00:21:44,361
visits a psychiatrist, and it turns
out the doctor is way too sexy

452
00:21:44,361 --> 00:21:46,171
that she ends up falling in love.

453
00:21:46,171 --> 00:21:48,091
It's very sexy and erotic.

454
00:21:48,091 --> 00:21:52,171
A thrilling twist awaits.

455
00:21:52,171 --> 00:21:55,241
Sexy and erotic.

456
00:21:59,631 --> 00:22:02,701
[Yeo Ha Ni's "Don't Let the Night Know
About Your Forbidden Love"]

457
00:22:02,701 --> 00:22:05,251
When I finally fall asleep,

458
00:22:06,071 --> 00:22:09,111
I start having the same dream.

459
00:22:11,941 --> 00:22:14,501
What kind of dream is it?

460
00:22:18,171 --> 00:22:19,961
[Holding breaths]

461
00:22:22,411 --> 00:22:24,861
[Voting starts]

462
00:22:25,921 --> 00:22:28,421
Huh? Why?

463
00:22:31,341 --> 00:22:33,571
[Already got 11 votes]

464
00:22:33,571 --> 00:22:34,801
[For those who can't sleep]

465
00:22:38,131 --> 00:22:40,861
Hi, it's me. Leave a message.

466
00:22:44,091 --> 00:22:45,721
[Shocked]

467
00:22:49,361 --> 00:22:52,631
What are you most afraid of?

468
00:22:55,981 --> 00:22:59,601
I feel like it's not a dream.

469
00:22:59,601 --> 00:23:01,341
[Don't Let the Night Know
About Your Forbidden Love]

470
00:23:01,341 --> 00:23:02,381
[Coming to Get You Soon]

471
00:23:02,381 --> 00:23:05,861
[She gets a chance to survive with 30 stops]

472
00:23:05,861 --> 00:23:07,231
Director Yeo Ha Ni.

473
00:23:07,231 --> 00:23:09,881
- Reminds me of Park Chan Wook.
- Like "Old Boy."

474
00:23:09,881 --> 00:23:11,821
It looked amazing.

475
00:23:11,821 --> 00:23:16,931
Maybe it's because I watched
so many teasers today,

476
00:23:16,931 --> 00:23:19,271
but the artistic ones are...

477
00:23:19,271 --> 00:23:22,951
How will she make 50 episodes of that?

478
00:23:22,951 --> 00:23:25,571
[Mixed opinions]

479
00:23:25,571 --> 00:23:28,271
I was shocked to see 30 votes.

480
00:23:28,271 --> 00:23:29,561
What did you guys think?

481
00:23:29,561 --> 00:23:32,191
If this weren't a short-form drama,

482
00:23:32,191 --> 00:23:35,421
I'd wonder why people would press stop.

483
00:23:35,421 --> 00:23:38,271
But since it is a short-form drama,

484
00:23:38,271 --> 00:23:40,171
I can understand why.

485
00:23:40,171 --> 00:23:43,011
[Accepting calmly]

486
00:23:43,011 --> 00:23:51,141
To be honest, this isn't suited
for the short drama viewers.

487
00:23:52,761 --> 00:23:54,861
[I can see that...]

488
00:23:54,861 --> 00:23:58,011
To be able to show my entire work,

489
00:23:58,011 --> 00:24:00,111
I thought I should show my style.

490
00:24:00,111 --> 00:24:04,151
So, I took a risk and went for all or nothing.

491
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:08,081
I actually have no regrets
because this is who I am.

492
00:24:08,081 --> 00:24:10,001
Beautiful back, blood, and sexiness.

493
00:24:10,001 --> 00:24:12,011
That's what I'm all about.

494
00:24:12,011 --> 00:24:13,671
My one regret is that...

495
00:24:13,671 --> 00:24:16,581
I didn't learn the short-form rhythm well enough.

496
00:24:16,581 --> 00:24:19,431
I'm not here to make art alone.

497
00:24:19,431 --> 00:24:22,311
I want my work to be loved by the public.

498
00:24:22,311 --> 00:24:25,941
So I think I was lacking in that regard.

499
00:24:25,941 --> 00:24:28,101
What I learned is that...

500
00:24:28,101 --> 00:24:31,201
directors and viewers see things differently.

501
00:24:31,201 --> 00:24:33,441
Of all the work we saw today,

502
00:24:33,441 --> 00:24:35,631
I found her editing style most unique.

503
00:24:35,631 --> 00:24:38,831
She has her own style.

504
00:24:38,831 --> 00:24:40,261
But for regular viewers,

505
00:24:40,261 --> 00:24:43,851
I don't think they like it
when the content feels heavy.

506
00:24:43,851 --> 00:24:47,711
It collected more stop counts than I thought.

507
00:24:47,711 --> 00:24:49,391
I was a bit disappointed.

508
00:24:49,391 --> 00:24:51,821
This is really hard.

509
00:24:51,821 --> 00:24:54,521
You thought you'd get it. But you don't.

510
00:24:54,521 --> 00:25:01,071
I'm learning to approach short dramas
differently than how I approach films.

511
00:25:01,071 --> 00:25:04,821
You need to keep the viewers hooked.

512
00:25:04,821 --> 00:25:08,621
Feed information. It's a huge
headache for the directors.

513
00:25:08,621 --> 00:25:10,871
But we consume them so casually.

514
