I get messages from my fans.

1040
00:48:25,201 --> 00:48:27,631
People often tease me by saying,

1041
00:48:27,631 --> 00:48:30,791
"I heard you're the Bong Joon Ho of BL."

1042
00:48:30,791 --> 00:48:34,641
[Known to be a reliable director]

1043
00:48:34,641 --> 00:48:37,181
My most recent one was "Secret Relationships."

1044
00:48:37,181 --> 00:48:41,401
The webtoon was so popular already.

1045
00:48:41,401 --> 00:48:44,391
[It ranked No. 1 as soon as it was released]

1046
00:48:44,391 --> 00:48:46,521
It was a Watcha exclusive.

1047
00:48:46,521 --> 00:48:49,951
I gained a lot of fans by ranking No. 1.

1048
00:48:49,951 --> 00:48:52,491
Is there a celebrity you look like?

1049
00:48:52,491 --> 00:48:53,981
This is...

1050
00:48:53,981 --> 00:48:57,441
It's kind of embarrassing.

1051
00:48:57,441 --> 00:49:00,111
When I was a kid,

1052
00:49:00,111 --> 00:49:04,961
people told me that I look like Shin Sae Kyeong.

1053
00:49:04,961 --> 00:49:08,521
I think thumbnail...

1054
00:49:08,521 --> 00:49:12,121
The title seems to have a strong selling point.

1055
00:49:12,121 --> 00:49:15,121
I'm very excited. It's not BL this time, is it?

1056
00:49:15,121 --> 00:49:19,041
I could've directed BL,

1057
00:49:19,041 --> 00:49:22,251
but the reason I chose "Joseon Man, MZ Woman" is

1058
00:49:22,251 --> 00:49:26,461
to prove that I'm a fan of the romance genre.

1059
00:49:26,461 --> 00:49:29,741
I chose to make this so I don't
get trapped in one genre.

1060
00:49:29,741 --> 00:49:32,571
Joseon's screwup king, Lee Hyeon

1061
00:49:32,571 --> 00:49:34,931
ends up landing in Hongdae.

1062
00:49:34,931 --> 00:49:38,121
He ends up living with an MZ part-timer.

1063
00:49:38,121 --> 00:49:42,081
Present-day and past clashes
in this time-slip comedy.

1064
00:49:42,081 --> 00:49:45,211
The screwup perfectly ends up in Hongdae.

1065
00:49:45,211 --> 00:49:46,831
I know. A good place to party.

1066
00:49:46,831 --> 00:49:48,771
It's a perfect place.

1067
00:49:48,771 --> 00:49:50,391
I love the setup.

1068
00:49:50,391 --> 00:49:54,331
Okay. Let's watch the teaser
for Director Yang Gyeong Hee.

1069
00:49:54,331 --> 00:49:57,461
Is she bleeding from her ear?

1070
00:49:57,461 --> 00:50:01,481
[What kind of rom-com did the
Bong Joon Ho of BL make?]

1071
00:50:01,481 --> 00:50:03,391
[Joseon Man, MZ Woman]

1072
00:50:03,391 --> 00:50:04,861
Wife?

1073
00:50:05,991 --> 00:50:07,641
"Wife"?

1074
00:50:08,361 --> 00:50:11,321
Who's this ancient scholar wannabe?

1075
00:50:17,571 --> 00:50:20,421
Oh, are you cosplaying?

1076
00:50:21,751 --> 00:50:23,521
[Joseon's king, Lee Hyeon, landed in Hongdae?]

1077
00:50:23,521 --> 00:50:25,721
I do not know why I ended up here,

1078
00:50:25,721 --> 00:50:28,461
but this world has a terrifying viral disease.

1079
00:50:28,461 --> 00:50:32,191
Even the name is tricky. MZ.

1080
00:50:32,191 --> 00:50:33,821
Cover yourself up immediately.

1081
00:50:33,821 --> 00:50:36,511
A woman should not show her shoulders.

1082
00:50:36,511 --> 00:50:40,291
Look at your wicked hair and fingernails.

1083
00:50:40,291 --> 00:50:42,781
[Something's off]

1084
00:50:43,341 --> 00:50:46,131
[Getting a bad feeling after the voting started]

1085
00:50:46,131 --> 00:50:48,771
[Hardening facial expression...]

1086
00:50:48,771 --> 00:50:52,721
Look at your wicked hair and fingernails.

1087
00:50:52,721 --> 00:50:54,031
Are you an evil creature?

1088
00:50:54,031 --> 00:50:56,741
Ahjussi, do you know me?

1089
00:50:57,381 --> 00:50:59,911
[The opposites meet!]

1090
00:50:59,911 --> 00:51:02,401
Body portrait? No thanks.

1091
00:51:02,401 --> 00:51:05,451
His MBTI isn't compatible. Not feeling it.

1092
00:51:06,301 --> 00:51:09,471
Are you choosing a man using this wicked panel?

1093
00:51:09,471 --> 00:51:12,741
- Do you think this makes sense?
- Darn it.

1094
00:51:12,741 --> 00:51:14,441
Is that why she was bleeding?

1095
00:51:14,441 --> 00:51:18,011
[Almost laughing]

1096
00:51:18,011 --> 00:51:19,621
I was so nervous.

1097
00:51:19,621 --> 00:51:23,821
I tried not to watch the stop count going up.

1098
00:51:23,821 --> 00:51:27,151
Evil, my foot. I'm looking for a fling.

1099
00:51:27,151 --> 00:51:29,741
What happened to this world?

1100
00:51:29,741 --> 00:51:32,171
You shouldn't judge a person by the appearance...

1101
00:51:32,171 --> 00:51:33,831
[Dating has to be casual. Why so serious?]

1102
00:51:42,151 --> 00:51:45,041
W-What are you doing? Already?

1103
00:51:47,531 --> 00:51:49,471
Get ready to go out now.

1104
00:51:49,471 --> 00:51:51,591
[Shy, but can't miss this amazing scene]

1105
00:51:51,591 --> 00:51:53,161
[The stop count froze because of the scene]

1106
00:51:53,161 --> 00:51:55,751
W-What are you doing? Already?

1107
00:51:58,121 --> 00:52:00,971
- Get ready to go out now.
- Geez!

1108
00:52:00,971 --> 00:52:02,711
Get out of here!

1109
00:52:02,711 --> 00:52:05,371
Can this cohabitation go well?

1110
00:52:05,371 --> 00:52:08,121
[Joseon Man, MZ Woman]

1111
00:52:10,831 --> 00:52:14,101
- It's well-made.
- Time flew by again.

1112
00:52:14,101 --> 00:52:16,741
You get a chance to survive.

1113
00:52:16,741 --> 00:52:21,521
I'm noticing it again this time.
The ones with experience

1114
00:52:21,521 --> 00:52:24,031
definitely have a similar touch.

1115
00:52:24,031 --> 00:52:27,251
And they all have a certain level of quality.

1116
00:52:27,251 --> 00:52:29,331
Of course, the plot was...

1117
00:52:29,331 --> 00:52:32,721
It's very familiar to us,

1118
00:52:32,721 --> 00:52:36,261
but if you get to make this later,

1119
00:52:36,261 --> 00:52:40,411
I'd like you to add something new.

1120
00:52:40,411 --> 00:52:44,031
And your specialty,

1121
00:52:44,031 --> 00:52:47,771
- BL can be added to.
- I'm curious to see that, too.

1122
00:52:47,771 --> 00:52:49,861
There could be something later.

1123
00:52:49,861 --> 00:52:53,351
Director Yang's work is known to have

1124
00:52:53,351 --> 00:52:55,381
a beautiful look to it.

1125
00:52:55,381 --> 00:52:58,591
Did you notice that, Director Lee?

1126
00:52:58,591 --> 00:53:01,131
Yes, it was beautiful, but...

1127
00:53:01,131 --> 00:53:06,821
The familiarity of time slip rom-com

1128
00:53:06,821 --> 00:53:09,971
can be both good and bad.

1129
00:53:09,971 --> 00:53:14,651
Let's see how you overcome this.

1130
00:53:14,651 --> 00:53:16,371
I'll look forward to it.

1131
00:53:16,371 --> 00:53:18,071
Thank you.

1132
00:53:18,851 --> 00:53:21,331
I should've worked harder as a director.

1133
00:53:21,331 --> 00:53:23,391
I should've shown something more innovative.

1134
00:53:23,391 --> 00:53:27,241
I'm not satisfied with that aspect,

1135
00:53:27,241 --> 00:53:31,001
but I think the audience liked it.

1136
00:53:31,001 --> 00:53:34,621
I got 16 votes.

1137
00:53:34,621 --> 00:53:37,461
I think some were from the directors.

1138
00:53:38,241 --> 00:53:41,381
Let's meet the next director.

1139
00:53:41,381 --> 00:53:43,861
The director of "Unfinished Film, Now Playing."

1140
00:53:43,861 --> 00:53:45,681
Please come up.

1141
00:53:45,681 --> 00:53:48,631
Wow, it's the youngest. Fighting, fighting!

1142
00:53:48,631 --> 00:53:50,831
[An adorable director appears]

1143
00:53:50,831 --> 00:53:52,311
What? There's more.

1144
00:53:52,311 --> 00:53:54,211
Your friends are here.

1145
00:53:54,211 --> 00:53:57,301
[Coming out]

1146
00:53:57,301 --> 00:53:59,091
The friends are here.

1147
00:53:59,091 --> 00:54:00,341
The friends are here.

1148
00:54:00,341 --> 00:54:03,111
One of them is a ninth-grader.

1149
00:54:03,111 --> 00:54:06,231
Ninth-grader, 10th-grader, and 11th-grader.

1150
00:54:06,231 --> 00:54:09,481
Hello, we're "Million-Volt Genius Club."

1151
00:54:09,481 --> 00:54:12,231
Oh Hae On, Ra Yun Seo, and Choi Shin Yul.

1152
00:54:12,231 --> 00:54:16,401
We met at a middle school club.

1153
00:54:16,401 --> 00:54:21,491
Everything started then,
and we made this short together, too.

1154
00:54:21,491 --> 00:54:24,001
Why do you want to become a director?

1155
00:54:24,001 --> 00:54:25,451
It's a little embarrassing.

1156
00:54:25,451 --> 00:54:30,761
I heard the filmmaking club
gives you free tteokbokki.

1157
00:54:30,761 --> 00:54:33,821
[Can't pass up on tteokbokki at her age]

1158
00:54:33,821 --> 00:54:35,671
That's how everything starts.

1159
00:54:35,671 --> 00:54:36,871
That's understandable.

1160
00:54:36,871 --> 00:54:38,931
I can't press the button with this one.

1161
00:54:38,931 --> 00:54:40,921
My reason for starting is...

1162
00:54:40,921 --> 00:54:43,431
I had a crush back then.

1163
00:54:43,431 --> 00:54:44,601
[Wow]

1164
00:54:44,601 --> 00:54:46,151
[Not stopping this story]

1165
00:54:46,151 --> 00:54:47,371
[Interested]

1166
00:54:47,371 --> 00:54:51,231
- This is more interesting.
- I heard he was joining this club.

1167
00:54:51,231 --> 00:54:55,361
So, I thought I could work with him there.

1168
00:54:55,361 --> 00:54:57,341
- That was the idea.
- So fun!

1169
00:54:57,341 --> 00:55:00,191
But after we did our first project,

1170
00:55:00,191 --> 00:55:03,071
he ended up in a different club.

1171
00:55:03,071 --> 00:55:05,771
I was the only one who stayed.

1172
00:55:05,771 --> 00:55:07,831
That's how I got to make a movie.

1173
00:55:07,831 --> 00:55:11,331
Since I was conveying my feelings in the movie,

1174
00:55:11,331 --> 00:55:15,401
I thought I could tell my story to other people.

1175
00:55:15,401 --> 00:55:17,781
I think I liked that feeling.

1176
00:55:17,781 --> 00:55:20,671
Look, they won the
grand prize at a film festival.

1177
00:55:20,671 --> 00:55:22,461
[2025 Songpa Youth Film Festival
Grand Prize winner]

1178
00:55:22,461 --> 00:55:24,711
[What will these talented
young filmmakers show us?]

1179
00:55:24,711 --> 00:55:28,581
A meek high-schooler, Seo Jun, who sees ghosts

1180
00:55:28,581 --> 00:55:31,371
met a ghost named Shin Yul and made a pact.

1181
00:55:31,371 --> 00:55:34,711
While encountering other ghosts at school,

1182
00:55:34,711 --> 00:55:39,221
he investigates her death
in this mystery fantasy.

1183
00:55:39,221 --> 00:55:41,451
[Unfinished Film, Now Playing]

1184
00:55:41,451 --> 00:55:43,421
[Million-Volt Genius Club's
"Unfinished Film, Now Playing"]

1185
00:55:43,421 --> 00:55:47,731
You went to a school like this,
or you're attending one now.

1186
00:55:47,731 --> 00:55:49,471
[Impressive first scene]

1187
00:55:49,471 --> 00:55:51,181
Drone.

1188
00:55:51,181 --> 00:55:52,741
You know what?

1189
00:55:52,741 --> 00:55:55,281
There's a ghost map for our school.

1190
00:56:02,021 --> 00:56:03,971
What?

1191
00:56:10,331 --> 00:56:12,211
[I'm scared]

1192
00:56:12,211 --> 00:56:13,711
[What?]

1193
00:56:31,661 --> 00:56:34,171
Aren't you curious to hear...

1194
00:56:34,171 --> 00:56:38,731
a ghost story told by a ghost?

1195
00:56:38,731 --> 00:56:40,501
[Stop count: 21]

1196
00:56:40,501 --> 00:56:42,521
[Judging finished]

1197
00:56:42,521 --> 00:56:44,581
Huh? Is it over?

1198
00:56:44,581 --> 00:56:46,461
[The scaredy-cat man kept his eyes half-closed]

1199
00:56:46,461 --> 00:56:49,781
You get a chance to survive with 21 stops.

1200
00:56:49,781 --> 00:56:51,231
Congratulations.

1201
00:56:51,231 --> 00:56:52,821
[A campus horror made by young talents]

1202
00:56:52,821 --> 00:56:54,961
Director Oh Hae On, congratulations.

1203
00:56:54,961 --> 00:56:57,881
I'm sorry, but I couldn't watch it.

1204
00:56:57,881 --> 00:57:00,881
- Why?
- I can't watch stuff with ghosts.

1205
00:57:00,881 --> 00:57:03,731
- You only heard it?
- I opened my eyes halfway

1206
00:57:03,731 --> 00:57:06,461
and closed them whenever
there was a ghost, but it won't stop.

1207
00:57:06,461 --> 00:57:09,191
[Peeping]

1208
00:57:09,191 --> 00:57:12,861
- That's why you asked if it was over?
- Yes, I couldn't watch it.

1209
00:57:12,861 --> 00:57:16,531
In the beginning, we saw a prop.

1210
00:57:16,531 --> 00:57:17,971
What was it?

1211
00:57:17,971 --> 00:57:22,461
We made those props ourselves.

1212
00:57:22,461 --> 00:57:26,521
We made the map and notebook
with the drawing of the school.

1213
00:57:26,521 --> 00:57:29,441
We drew the ghost, too. We made all the props.

1214
00:57:29,441 --> 00:57:31,301
I see.

1215
00:57:31,301 --> 00:57:36,041
It's a story people your age
would be very interested in.

1216
00:57:36,041 --> 00:57:37,611
They love ghost stories.

1217
00:57:37,611 --> 00:57:39,971
School and ghosts.

1218
00:57:39,971 --> 00:57:42,241
[After the teen directors' ghost story]

1219
00:57:42,241 --> 00:57:45,631
"Jushin High Horror: The Night Returns."

1220
00:57:46,181 --> 00:57:47,231
[Jushin High Horror: The Night Returns]

1221
00:57:47,231 --> 00:57:50,271
Never look back.

1222
00:57:50,271 --> 00:57:52,961
[A campus horror movie where the
bully gets punished in Death Game]

1223
00:57:52,961 --> 00:57:56,011
Don't ever look in the mirror.

1224
00:57:56,521 --> 00:57:59,171
[Hating it]

1225
00:57:59,171 --> 00:58:01,211
[The scary pacing makes your heart race]

1226
00:58:01,961 --> 00:58:04,741
Breathe quietly.

1227
00:58:05,661 --> 00:58:08,521
Don't ever look back.

1228
00:58:08,521 --> 00:58:11,841
Don't ever look in the mirror.

1229
00:58:11,841 --> 00:58:15,141
Checking attendance for Class 10th-3.

1230
00:58:15,141 --> 00:58:17,221
Baek Hee Ra.

1231
00:58:18,761 --> 00:58:20,621
Im Jin Ju.

1232
00:58:22,951 --> 00:58:26,981
[Can't look away]

1233
00:58:26,981 --> 00:58:30,141
Checking attendance for Class 10th-3.

1234
00:58:30,141 --> 00:58:32,401
Baek Hee Ra.

1235
00:58:33,331 --> 00:58:35,451
[The stop count won't stop]

1236
00:58:35,451 --> 00:58:37,391
Im Jin Ju.

1237
00:58:40,131 --> 00:58:42,181
Shin Ye Ri.

1238
00:58:44,281 --> 00:58:46,281
Shin Ye Ri.

1239
00:58:46,281 --> 00:58:48,561
Shin Ye Ri.

1240
00:58:48,561 --> 00:58:50,121
Shin Ye Ri.

1241
00:58:50,121 --> 00:58:59,921
Shin Ye Ri. Shin Ye Ri. Shin Ye Ri. Shin Ye Ri...

1242
00:59:02,311 --> 00:59:04,371
Attendance confirmed.

1243
00:59:05,411 --> 00:59:07,081
[Gosh!]

1244
00:59:07,081 --> 00:59:08,661
Wow.

1245
00:59:08,661 --> 00:59:10,491
[Painful for the faint-hearted]

1246
00:59:10,491 --> 00:59:13,721
What? It's scary.

1247
00:59:13,721 --> 00:59:17,331
[Spooked]

1248
00:59:17,331 --> 00:59:19,051
I told you not to look back.

1249
00:59:19,051 --> 00:59:21,371
You looked back. You looked back...

1250
00:59:21,371 --> 00:59:24,421
The class will start now.

1251
00:59:24,421 --> 00:59:25,731
[Jushin High Horror: The Night Returns]

1252
00:59:26,341 --> 00:59:29,451
[He wanted to go home for 90 seconds]

1253
00:59:29,451 --> 00:59:32,381
Wow, I got sucked in.

1254
00:59:32,381 --> 00:59:35,861
[The sighs of relief prove
the overwhelming horror]

1255
00:59:35,861 --> 00:59:38,081
It was so scary. Were you okay, Tae Hyun?

1256
00:59:38,081 --> 00:59:40,331
I kept closing and opening my eyes,

1257
00:59:40,331 --> 00:59:42,341
- but I didn't see one.
- Wasn't it even scarier?

1258
00:59:42,341 --> 00:59:45,921
And I got spooked at the very end.

1259
00:59:46,571 --> 00:59:48,451
Geez.

1260
00:59:49,221 --> 00:59:50,971
I got spooked.

1261
00:59:50,971 --> 00:59:54,111
[Who's the director who spooked Tae Hyun?]

1262
00:59:54,111 --> 00:59:57,311
I worked on a film set for about 10 years.

1263
00:59:57,311 --> 01:00:01,661
I tried making a YouTube video
with my phone one day.

1264
01:00:01,661 --> 01:00:04,941
Since then, I got interested in short dramas.

1265
01:00:04,941 --> 01:00:06,591
[Director Eun Jong Hun]

1266
01:00:06,591 --> 01:00:09,361
Did you shoot with a smartphone this time, too?

1267
01:00:09,361 --> 01:00:13,631
Yes. I filmed it with an iPhone 16 Pro.

1268
01:00:13,631 --> 01:00:17,601
[The king of budget filmmaking,
perfect for the short-form era]

1269
01:00:20,721 --> 01:00:24,631
[He doesn't let equipment limit him]

1270
01:00:25,291 --> 01:00:29,431
[He spooked everyone with just a smartphone]

1271
01:00:30,231 --> 01:00:31,931
Wouldn't you say it was well-received?

1272
01:00:31,931 --> 01:00:34,561
- It was.
- I held my breath watching it, too.

1273
01:00:34,561 --> 01:00:36,301
Right.

1274
01:00:36,301 --> 01:00:41,751
[Both Eun Jong Hun and Oh Hae On got 21 stops]

1275
01:00:41,751 --> 01:00:45,801
Currently, the viewing times have been

1276
01:00:45,801 --> 01:00:47,621
very much neck and neck.

1277
01:00:47,621 --> 01:00:48,891
Really?

1278
01:00:48,891 --> 01:00:52,071
It might be a matter of 0.1 seconds.

1279
01:00:52,071 --> 01:00:55,031
[21 votes / 21 votes / 22 votes / 23 votes]

1280
01:00:55,031 --> 01:00:59,021
[The viewing time will determine the ranking]

1281
01:00:59,021 --> 01:01:02,561
You can't relax because
your video wasn't stopped.

1282
01:01:02,561 --> 01:01:05,421
Right. It's not over until it's over.

1283
01:01:05,421 --> 01:01:07,761
[It's not over until it's over]

1284
01:01:09,201 --> 01:01:11,841
[Of the highlights that haven't been played yet]

1285
01:01:11,841 --> 01:01:13,901
[This thumbnail sticks out a lot]

1286
01:01:14,711 --> 01:01:17,561
- It's cool.
- Looks like a video game teaser.

1287
01:01:17,561 --> 01:01:19,601
The one who used AI?

1288
01:01:19,601 --> 01:01:21,021
Yes.

1289
01:01:21,021 --> 01:01:24,431
100% AI. He's an AI master.

1290
01:01:25,561 --> 01:01:28,121
He majored in AI, huh?

1291
01:01:28,121 --> 01:01:30,541
[Who's this likable-looking man?]

1292
01:01:30,541 --> 01:01:33,511
I have about 240,000 subscribers.

1293
01:01:33,511 --> 01:01:36,911
I'm an AI creator, Oh Han Byeol.

1294
01:01:36,911 --> 01:01:39,851
I create content using AI.

1295
01:01:39,851 --> 01:01:42,931
I make a lot of ones with miniatures.

1296
01:01:42,931 --> 01:01:45,901
The theme is called "mini republic."

1297
01:01:45,901 --> 01:01:49,121
Miniature people are living in the human world.

1298
01:01:49,121 --> 01:01:53,951
The most popular one had 120 million views.

1299
01:01:53,951 --> 01:01:55,891
It went viral.

1300
01:01:58,171 --> 01:02:00,951
I combined video game graphics and AI.

1301
01:02:00,951 --> 01:02:05,471
I give lectures at schools,
corporations, and organizations.

1302
01:02:05,471 --> 01:02:10,851
[Won many AI-related awards]

1303
01:02:10,851 --> 01:02:13,851
Wow, this is fascinating.

1304
01:02:13,851 --> 01:02:15,461
It's a double-edged sword.

1305
01:02:15,461 --> 01:02:18,441
Please introduce your short drama.

1306
01:02:18,441 --> 01:02:21,401
The miniature people live inside a wall.

1307
01:02:21,401 --> 01:02:23,611
They don't know about the outside world,

1308
01:02:23,611 --> 01:02:26,811
but they encounter a boy from the outside.

1309
01:02:26,811 --> 01:02:29,261
They learn the secrets about their existence

1310
01:02:29,261 --> 01:02:31,991
and the secrets inside the castle wall.

1311
01:02:31,991 --> 01:02:34,011
It's an adventure fantasy drama.

1312
01:02:34,011 --> 01:02:37,031
You created the entire short drama on AI, right?

1313
01:02:37,031 --> 01:02:40,231
That's correct. I created everything on AI.

1314
01:02:40,231 --> 01:02:42,221
I produced the whole video myself.

1315
01:02:42,221 --> 01:02:48,281
Did your vast imagination come to life?

1316
01:02:48,281 --> 01:02:50,731
Let's watch the teaser now.

1317
01:02:50,731 --> 01:02:53,171
Please play the video.

1318
01:02:54,361 --> 01:02:56,361
As an AI creator,

1319
01:02:56,361 --> 01:03:01,081
I'll be able to show people something new.

1320
01:03:01,081 --> 01:03:03,751
I'm curious. It's a fantasy.

1321
01:03:04,531 --> 01:03:07,611
[Will his work make the other directors nervous?]

1322
01:03:07,611 --> 01:03:11,541
[The Wall Dwellers]

1323
01:03:11,541 --> 01:03:15,161
[Oh Han Byeol's "The Wall Dwellers"]

1324
01:03:21,611 --> 01:03:23,011
How dare you try to kill me?

1325
01:03:23,011 --> 01:03:25,541
[A mysterious world created by AI]

1326
01:03:28,131 --> 01:03:31,261
What could be behind this wall?

1327
01:03:31,261 --> 01:03:33,541
I'll be back for sure.

1328
01:03:33,541 --> 01:03:35,601
Do you have to go?

1329
01:03:39,731 --> 01:03:40,531
[Voting starts]

1330
01:03:40,531 --> 01:03:43,031
Why are we here?

1331
01:03:44,921 --> 01:03:46,651
[The secret inside the wall]

1332
01:03:46,651 --> 01:03:49,421
[Voting starts]

1333
01:03:51,231 --> 01:03:54,981
[The stop count floods in
for the flawless AI creation?]

1334
01:03:55,631 --> 01:03:56,801
[Tilting head]

1335
01:04:06,261 --> 01:04:08,221
Ha Ru!

1336
01:04:08,221 --> 01:04:11,021
Come to your senses, please!

1337
01:04:17,871 --> 01:04:23,941
[The stop count is skyrocketing]

1338
01:04:24,801 --> 01:04:28,421
Did it really exist?

1339
01:04:46,121 --> 01:04:48,661
[The Wall Dwellers -
First look on Director's Arena]

1340
01:04:48,661 --> 01:04:50,221
Yes.

1341
01:04:50,221 --> 01:04:54,321
Director Oh Han Byeol, with 22 stops,

1342
01:04:54,321 --> 01:04:56,621
you get a chance to survive. Congratulations.

1343
01:04:56,621 --> 01:04:58,241
Thank you.

1344
01:04:59,401 --> 01:05:02,891
It was the first 100% AI short drama.

1345
01:05:02,891 --> 01:05:05,381
I didn't find it very original.

1346
01:05:05,381 --> 01:05:09,161
It was something I've seen a lot.

1347
01:05:09,161 --> 01:05:10,991
This is a matter of taste,

1348
01:05:10,991 --> 01:05:13,861
but the AI videos give off this eerie feeling.

1349
01:05:13,861 --> 01:05:16,761
I'm very critical of that.

1350
01:05:16,761 --> 01:05:18,431
It was a bit disappointing.

1351
01:05:18,431 --> 01:05:21,571
When I heard it was 100% AI,

1352
01:05:21,571 --> 01:05:23,781
I was like, "What's that like?"

1353
01:05:23,781 --> 01:05:25,561
But when I saw the video,

1354
01:05:25,561 --> 01:05:27,891
it was something we've seen a lot.

1355
01:05:27,891 --> 01:05:30,931
- Like it's from a game.
- Right.

1356
01:05:30,931 --> 01:05:32,831
I wanted to say something nice,

1357
01:05:32,831 --> 01:05:34,821
but in the end...

1358
01:05:34,821 --> 01:05:36,741
there wasn't much.

1359
01:05:36,741 --> 01:05:41,471
It wasn't something new.

1360
01:05:41,471 --> 01:05:46,301
I was curious how this would work in short form.

1361
01:05:46,301 --> 01:05:48,471
I'm not sure if I missed something, but

1362
01:05:48,471 --> 01:05:50,641
I can't figure out the story.

1363
01:05:50,641 --> 01:05:53,291
- Oh, I see.
- But using technology on top of that

1364
01:05:53,291 --> 01:05:55,851
made it feel a bit showy.

1365
01:05:55,851 --> 01:05:58,521
That was what I was disappointed about.

1366
01:05:58,521 --> 01:06:00,971
Wow, so negative.

1367
01:06:00,971 --> 01:06:02,711
[Even the AI master couldn't
overcome the wall of short drama]

1368
01:06:02,711 --> 01:06:06,041
I only emphasized that it was made with AI,

1369
01:06:06,041 --> 01:06:10,021
but I should've balanced it
with good storytelling.

1370
01:06:10,021 --> 01:06:12,521
I think I failed to strike that balance.

1371
01:06:12,521 --> 01:06:16,161
Let's meet the next director, then.

1372
01:06:16,161 --> 01:06:18,271
"Is This Really an Accident?"

1373
01:06:18,271 --> 01:06:20,171
That thumbnail is catching my eye.

1374
01:06:20,171 --> 01:06:22,491
Nice to meet you.

1375
01:06:22,491 --> 01:06:24,741
[Who's this director?]

1376
01:06:24,741 --> 01:06:28,641
She worked on "Extreme Job" with Director Lee.

1377
01:06:28,641 --> 01:06:32,991
I first worked with Director Lee in 2016.

1378
01:06:32,991 --> 01:06:35,241
It was for "Positive Physique."

1379
01:06:35,241 --> 01:06:37,291
Has it been nine years?

1380
01:06:37,291 --> 01:06:40,701
The genre I chose is black comedy.

1381
01:06:40,701 --> 01:06:42,531
[A dysfunctional family works
in a body processing part-time job]

1382
01:06:42,531 --> 01:06:44,511
[Gets sucked into the world
of crime in this black comedy]

1383
01:06:44,511 --> 01:06:46,171
Geez.

1384
01:06:48,861 --> 01:06:50,521
[Hmm...]

1385
01:06:50,521 --> 01:06:53,441
[The assistant director's passion project]

1386
01:06:53,931 --> 01:06:56,161
[But the stop count keeps going up]

1387
01:06:58,571 --> 01:07:01,801
You get a chance to survive
with 26 stops. Congratulations.

1388
01:07:01,801 --> 01:07:03,371
[Kim Yi An is in danger of being eliminated]

1389
01:07:04,041 --> 01:07:06,111
It wasn't exactly impactful.

1390
01:07:06,111 --> 01:07:09,251
It didn't quite hook me.

1391
01:07:09,251 --> 01:07:12,041
Since you focused on the
cinematography and editing,

1392
01:07:12,041 --> 01:07:16,461
you didn't tell us what the story was about.

1393
01:07:16,461 --> 01:07:17,821
That was disappointing.

1394
01:07:17,821 --> 01:07:20,191
- Thank you.
- Congrats.

1395
01:07:20,191 --> 01:07:25,501
Hello, I'm a director and actor, Nam Yeon Woo.

1396
01:07:25,501 --> 01:07:27,481
[The End of the Role]

1397
01:07:27,481 --> 01:07:29,881
[A rookie actress plans revenge
on a lover who betrayed her]

1398
01:07:29,881 --> 01:07:32,501
[She turns into a monster
in this psychological thriller]

1399
01:07:32,981 --> 01:07:35,201
[Icy silence...]

1400
01:07:37,171 --> 01:07:40,291
[The teaser is reaching the maximum stop count]

1401
01:07:40,291 --> 01:07:42,211
[Stop count: 35]

1402
01:07:42,211 --> 01:07:43,511
[Stop]

1403
01:07:43,511 --> 01:07:45,121
- Really?
- Why?

1404
01:07:45,121 --> 01:07:50,771
You put together a bunch of stills,
but they weren't exactly very impactful.

1405
01:07:50,771 --> 01:07:56,011
I personally struggled to understand the story.

1406
01:07:56,011 --> 01:07:59,991
I thought it wasn't quite engaging enough.

1407
01:07:59,991 --> 01:08:02,211
I was so confused.

1408
01:08:02,211 --> 01:08:07,271
I realized it wasn't the content I thought it was.

1409
01:08:07,271 --> 01:08:10,881
Each second in short dramas is

1410
01:08:10,881 --> 01:08:13,721
very different than in films or TV dramas.

1411
01:08:14,691 --> 01:08:15,781
It's hard.

1412
01:08:15,781 --> 01:08:17,811
It's easy to consume as viewers,

1413
01:08:17,811 --> 01:08:20,951
- but it must be so tough for directors.
- Of course.

1414
01:08:20,951 --> 01:08:24,811
The viewers seem to have strong tastes.

1415
01:08:24,811 --> 01:08:26,851
I think it's nice for that reason.

1416
01:08:26,851 --> 01:08:31,501
Yes, that's how we find high-quality work.

1417
01:08:31,501 --> 01:08:34,611
Let's meet the next director.

1418
01:08:34,611 --> 01:08:36,271
I was so curious about this one.

1419
01:08:36,271 --> 01:08:39,461
The director of "We Take Care of Anything,"
please come out.

1420
01:08:39,461 --> 01:08:43,151
The director of "We Take Care of Anything,"
please come out.

1421
01:08:43,151 --> 01:08:46,051
[A very familiar hit-making actor!]

1422
01:08:46,051 --> 01:08:47,851
- Huh?
- What?

1423
01:08:47,851 --> 01:08:49,901
[A warm welcome for this person]

1424
01:08:49,901 --> 01:08:52,531
The actual troubleshooter is here.

1425
01:08:52,531 --> 01:08:54,441
[Here to troubleshoot the vibe in the studio]

1426
01:08:55,691 --> 01:08:58,901
- Mr. Choi.
- Mr. Choi Gwi Hwa.

1427
01:08:58,901 --> 01:09:01,521
A great actor joined the directors' competition.

1428
01:09:01,521 --> 01:09:04,561
I'm very much looking forward to his work.

1429
01:09:04,561 --> 01:09:07,481
[Can't believe it]

1430
01:09:07,481 --> 01:09:10,851
Hello, I've been acting for 30 years now.

1431
01:09:10,851 --> 01:09:12,841
I'm actor Choi Gwi Hwa. Nice to meet you.

1432
01:09:12,841 --> 01:09:16,781
[Welcome]

1433
01:09:16,781 --> 01:09:20,081
I see a cool title before the name "Choi Gwi Hwa."

1434
01:09:20,081 --> 01:09:22,611
It says, "Actor of 30 million audience."

1435
01:09:22,611 --> 01:09:24,541
So cool.

1436
01:09:24,541 --> 01:09:26,421
[A scene stealer in Korean cinema!]

1437
01:09:26,421 --> 01:09:29,461
[Starting his journey to
become a hit-making director!]

1438
01:09:29,461 --> 01:09:32,561
[The die has been tossed]

1439
01:09:32,561 --> 01:09:34,271
An actor with a 30 million audience.

1440
01:09:34,271 --> 01:09:38,261
I'm curious why you want to make short dramas.

1441
01:09:38,261 --> 01:09:43,371
I've directed short films or online commercials.

1442
01:09:43,371 --> 01:09:44,631
You did.

1443
01:09:44,631 --> 01:09:47,441
Whenever I wanted to come up with a fun story,

1444
01:09:47,441 --> 01:09:49,181
I turned it into a film.

1445
01:09:49,181 --> 01:09:52,601
And then I heard about this audition.

1446
01:09:52,601 --> 01:09:54,811
I happened to have something written.

1447
01:09:54,811 --> 01:09:57,741
- That's how I ended up here.
- I'm so glad you did.

1448
01:09:57,741 --> 01:10:01,931
You must feel pressured
as an actor-turned-director.

1449
01:10:01,931 --> 01:10:06,011
Since I'm not debuting with a commercial film,

1450
01:10:06,011 --> 01:10:07,921
I don't feel as pressured.

1451
01:10:07,921 --> 01:10:09,821
But when actors make attempts like this,

1452
01:10:09,821 --> 01:10:13,051
some people think negatively.

1453
01:10:13,051 --> 01:10:16,301
I think that's all in the past.

1454
01:10:16,301 --> 01:10:18,331
I don't think it's like that at all anymore.

1455
01:10:18,331 --> 01:10:22,211
- I agree.
- If you get a good result here,

1456
01:10:22,211 --> 01:10:26,121
I recommend you do both.

1457
01:10:26,121 --> 01:10:29,351
If there are people like that, prove them wrong.

1458
01:10:29,351 --> 01:10:31,521
I'm okay.

1459
01:10:32,341 --> 01:10:34,381
Everyone else's looked so cool.

1460
01:10:34,381 --> 01:10:37,011
- But mine is so...
- It actually stands out.

1461
01:10:37,011 --> 01:10:38,671
Since we're seeing nothing but that.

1462
01:10:38,671 --> 01:10:40,511
I want to know the intention.

1463
01:10:40,511 --> 01:10:43,391
I'm curious what we're about to see.

1464
01:10:43,391 --> 01:10:45,751
[Dongtan, Gyeonggi-do]

1465
01:10:45,751 --> 01:10:48,931
[The shooting prep is underway]

1466
01:10:49,421 --> 01:10:51,921
[And there's one man who's the busiest]

1467
01:10:52,661 --> 01:10:54,501
[Actor Choi Gwi Hwa]

1468
01:10:54,501 --> 01:10:55,871
[Director Choi Gwi Hwa]

1469
01:10:56,411 --> 01:10:58,531
[Director Choi's duty 1: Get props]

1470
01:10:58,531 --> 01:11:01,331
[Checking them thoroughly]

1471
01:11:02,021 --> 01:11:05,011
[Director Choi's duty 2: Setting up the location]

1472
01:11:05,721 --> 01:11:08,821
[Director Choi's duty 3: Table read]

1473
01:11:08,821 --> 01:11:12,321
If you don't exaggerate, it won't come across.

1474
01:11:12,321 --> 01:11:16,331
The direction of this short drama
is most important.

1475
01:11:16,331 --> 01:11:20,401
I think we need to communicate the work's charm.

1476
01:11:20,401 --> 01:11:23,801
I've been picturing it in my head for days.

1477
01:11:23,801 --> 01:11:25,921
Of course, there will be variables.

1478
01:11:25,921 --> 01:11:28,731
There always are on sets.

1479
01:11:28,731 --> 01:11:32,611
If we come across them,
we'll just skip the scene.

1480
01:11:33,321 --> 01:11:35,251
[Shooting begins]

1481
01:11:35,251 --> 01:11:36,971
Action.

1482
01:11:38,481 --> 01:11:40,201
Hold on, hold on.

1483
01:11:40,201 --> 01:11:41,981
Hold on. You know...

1484
01:11:41,981 --> 01:11:44,871
[Full of passion, more than he lets on]

1485
01:11:44,871 --> 01:11:46,351
Can we...

1486
01:11:47,181 --> 01:11:50,011
Can you lay it more flat? More.

1487
01:11:50,011 --> 01:11:51,221
A little more.

1488
01:11:51,221 --> 01:11:53,991
How about we do this? Follow him and...

1489
01:11:53,991 --> 01:11:56,721
[Where should I go this time?]

1490
01:11:56,721 --> 01:11:58,831
I hear this place is really good.

1491
01:11:58,831 --> 01:12:01,511
Approach a little closer...

1492
01:12:01,511 --> 01:12:04,001
and say, "I'll bite you."

1493
01:12:05,411 --> 01:12:08,081
[His passion is unstoppable]

1494
01:12:08,081 --> 01:12:10,931
[His film set is full of sincere passion]

1495
01:12:10,931 --> 01:12:13,671
Whether he's acting or directing,

1496
01:12:13,671 --> 01:12:17,411
he uses 120% of his passion.

1497
01:12:17,411 --> 01:12:19,361
[Don't say you won't direct]

1498
01:12:19,361 --> 01:12:20,971
Cut.

1499
01:12:20,971 --> 01:12:23,011
Nice. Very nice.

1500
01:12:23,011 --> 01:12:26,091
[What kind of teaser did his passion create?]

1501
01:12:26,091 --> 01:12:27,701
It's like a detective agency.

1502
01:12:27,701 --> 01:12:30,241
He invites his clients to the restaurant

1503
01:12:30,241 --> 01:12:32,081
and finds a solution with them.

1504
01:12:32,081 --> 01:12:33,771
In this short drama,

1505
01:12:33,771 --> 01:12:37,521
a client commissions him with an adultery case.

1506
01:12:37,521 --> 01:12:40,081
He brings the cheating man and woman in

1507
01:12:40,081 --> 01:12:41,961
and finds evidence there.

1508
01:12:41,961 --> 01:12:43,771
It's a chaotic drama.

1509
01:12:43,771 --> 01:12:47,501
He must've created chapters.

1510
01:12:47,501 --> 01:12:49,711
[10 seconds to his directorial debut]

1511
01:12:49,711 --> 01:12:51,621
[Heart beating]

1512
01:12:51,621 --> 01:12:55,211
[Getting ready to watch]

1513
01:12:55,211 --> 01:12:56,981
[Already entertained]

1514
01:12:56,981 --> 01:12:59,421
I'm certain that it has the edge.

1515
01:12:59,421 --> 01:13:01,601
I know this will work.

1516
01:13:01,601 --> 01:13:04,501
It will work with young audiences.

1517
01:13:04,501 --> 01:13:09,451
[What kind of teaser did he create?]

1518
01:13:10,081 --> 01:13:12,831
Let's meet the next director.

1519
01:13:12,831 --> 01:13:15,371
- KAIST?
- SBS drama producer?

1520
01:13:15,371 --> 01:13:17,181
AI trainer with 900,000 views.

1521
01:13:17,181 --> 01:13:18,561
About 150 projects.

1522
01:13:18,561 --> 01:13:20,271
They look very familiar.

1523
01:13:20,271 --> 01:13:22,791
More talented people?

1524
01:13:22,791 --> 01:13:24,351
I feel so insecure.

1525
01:13:24,351 --> 01:13:27,371
I hope I spike everyone's dopamine.

1526
01:13:27,371 --> 01:13:28,961
[The dopamine reached its peak]

1527
01:13:28,961 --> 01:13:31,341
It's almost there!

1528
01:13:31,341 --> 01:13:34,031
[LOL]

1529
01:13:34,031 --> 01:13:35,331
This is what short drama is.

1530
01:13:35,331 --> 01:13:36,581
It was so shocking.

1531
01:13:36,581 --> 01:13:37,931
[And]

1532
01:13:37,931 --> 01:13:39,661
Finally, he's here.

1533
01:13:39,661 --> 01:13:41,361
[Finally showing up]

1534
01:13:41,361 --> 01:13:44,081
It was Director Lee Joo Seung.

1535
01:13:44,821 --> 01:13:46,501
[The stop count is skyrocketing]

1536
01:13:46,501 --> 01:13:48,061
I'm screwed.

1537
01:13:48,061 --> 01:13:50,531
I'm getting eliminated.

1538
01:13:50,531 --> 01:13:52,271
To be honest, I pressed stop.

1539
01:13:52,271 --> 01:13:54,551
Whether Lee Joo Seung directed or not...

1540
01:13:54,551 --> 01:13:56,491
I was like, "Why didn't I enjoy this?"

1541
01:13:56,491 --> 01:13:58,421
It was overall safe.

1542
01:13:58,421 --> 01:14:00,111
I want to go home.

1543
01:14:00,111 --> 01:14:03,381
Let's reveal the final result.

1544
01:14:03,381 --> 01:14:06,361
The last director to advance.

1545
01:14:06,361 --> 01:14:08,961
